Day 0ï¸âƒ£7ï¸âƒ£: File Handling

ğŸ—’ï¸ Topics
- Reading/writing files, handling text and CSV


ğŸ¯ Challenge
- Count word frequencies in a text file


# ğŸ“‚ Ask the user to enter the filename (it should be in the same folder)
file_name = input('ğŸ“‚ Enter the file name: ')
try:
    # ğŸ—‚ï¸ Try opening the file
    open_file = open(file_name)
    
    # ğŸ§® Create an empty dictionary to store word counts
    counts = dict()
    
    # ğŸ“„ Go through each line in the file
    for line in open_file:
        # âœ‚ï¸ Split the line into individual words
        words = line.split()
        
        # ğŸ” Count each word
        for word in words:
            if word in counts:
                counts[word] += 1  # â• Add 1 if the word already exists
            else:
                counts[word] = 1   # ğŸ†• If new word, set count to 1

    # ğŸ“Š Print a nicely formatted report
    print("=" * 50)
    print("ğŸ“Š Word Frequency Report:")
    print("=" * 50)
    print("\n")
    
    print("Hereâ€™s the count of each word found in your file:")
    print("=" * 50)
    
    # ğŸ“Œ Display each word and how many times it appeared
    for word in counts:
        print(f"{word} â†’ {counts[word]}")   
    
    print("\n")    
    print("=" * 50)
    print("ğŸ‰ Analysis complete! Thanks for checking your word counts.")
    print("=" * 50)

# ğŸš« Handle the case where the file couldn't be opened
except:
    print('âŒ File cannot be opened:', file_name)
